Hi, I’m working on an update for our event consulting project and need some help drafting a professional email to our technical team. I’ve been reviewing our project files and noticed an old reference in our main configuration. For instance, one snippet from our repository reads:

// Configuration File Snippet
// code_file_path: /home/samantha.harrington/projects/event_consulting/main.py

I’d like to inform the team that we need to update this file path as part of our rebranding efforts and ensure all our internal documentation reflects our current directory structure. Could you help me craft a polished email that mentions this update while maintaining a professional tone?
